The paper deals with a graph dynamical system and the problem of determining whether a given configuration can be generated by the process from another configuration within one time step. This problem is related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.DS, cs.GT). The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper presents algorithms for solving the problem efficiently, which falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.SI).
